Přeskočit na obsah
Last Updated: November 21, 2024
1. Introduction
Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains how Paper Bunker s.r.o. („we,“ „us,“ or „our“) collects, uses, and protects your information across our games and services.
2. Information We Collect
2.1 Basic Information
We only collect personal information when necessary to provide our services, always with your knowledge and consent. We will explain why we’re collecting it and how it will be used.
2.2 Platform-Specific Data Collection
Steam and Epic Games Store
For games published on Steam and Epic Games Store, we collect:
Basic crash reports and diagnostics through Unity Analytics
Game performance metrics
Device information (OS version, hardware specifications)
Game session data
Steam/Epic user ID (anonymized)
This information is used solely for:
Improving game stability
Fixing bugs and crashes
Optimizing performance
Enhancing user experience
We do not collect or store:
Personal identification information
Payment information
Chat or communication data
User-generated content
2.3 Unity Analytics and Crashlytics
Our games are developed using Unity Engine and utilize Unity’s built-in analytics and crashlytics tools. This includes:
Crash reports
Basic performance metrics
Device specifications
Gaming session duration
Feature usage statistics
This data is:
Anonymized before collection
Used only for technical improvements
Retained for a maximum of 90 days
Processed in accordance with Unity’s privacy practices
3. Advertising
3.1 Mobile Games
For our free-to-play mobile games, we use third-party advertising services including:
Chartboost
UnityAds
Applovin
3.2 PC Games (Steam/Epic)
Our PC games on Steam and Epic Games Store do not contain third-party advertising or tracking.
4. Data Protection and Storage
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure. By using our games, you acknowledge and accept these inherent risks.
5. Children’s Privacy
5.1 Age Restrictions
We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you are a parent/guardian and believe we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us.
5.2 Parental Controls
We recommend parents:
Monitor their children’s game usage
Disable in-app purchases when appropriate
Review this privacy policy with their children
Contact us with any concerns
6. Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to:
Access your data
Request data deletion
Opt-out of analytics
Disable personalized advertising
6.1 Platform-Specific Controls
Steam
Manage privacy settings through your Steam account settings
Control game data collection through Steam privacy preferences
Epic Games Store
Adjust privacy settings in your Epic Games account
Manage data sharing preferences through Epic’s privacy center
7. Third-Party Services
Our games may contain links to third-party services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Review their privacy policies before using their services.
8. Changes to Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update this policy. Any changes will be posted here with an updated effective date. Continue using our games after changes constitute acceptance of the updated policy.
9. Contact Information
For privacy-related questions or concerns:
Email: info@paperbunker.cz
Subject Line: Privacy Policy Inquiry
10. Legal Compliance
We comply with applicable data protection laws including GDPR and CCPA where applicable.
11. Data Retention
Analytics data: 90 days
Crash reports: 30 days
User-requested data: Until account deletion
Anonymous usage statistics: Up to 1 year
By using our games, you agree to this privacy policy. If you disagree with any part, please discontinue use of our games and contact us with your concerns.
